records.addlTxt:
Defendant Jovante Gerard Winston in court with attorney Leah R. Thomas.  Ronald Dague appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk ssm.  

Defendant changes his plea to GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty.   Defendant advised that if not a United States Citizen, deportation is possible.  Court found that defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights.  Guilty Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea.  Court found defendant guilty and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.  

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  Defendant sentenced to serve 9 MONTHS in the House of Correction with credit for 5 days time served.  Court STAYED the sentence and placed defendant on Probation with the State of Wisconsin, Department of Corrections for a period of 1 YEAR.
Conditions:  
*  Letter of apology to Elaine H.;
*  Maintain absolute sobriety to be monitored by random urine screens;
*  AODA assessment/treatment deemed appropriate;
*  Obtain GED/Barber/Cosmetology;
*  Complete a parenting class;
*  Perform 25 hours of community service;
*  Serve 16 days in the House of Correction with huber for work;
*  Serve 14 days in the House of Correction; sentence stayed and to be used by agent for any violations;
*  Submit DNA sample;
*  Pay all costs and surcharges or, if not paid, convert to a civil judgment.
